Enzyme differentiates arbitrary multivariate vector functions as the most general case in automatic differentiation \[ f: \mathbb{R}^n \rightarrow \mathbb{R}^m, y = f(x) \] For simplicity we define a vector function with \(m=1\). However, this tutorial can easily be applied to arbitrary \(m \in \mathbb{N}\). fn f(x: &[f32], y: &mut f32) { y = x[0] * x[0] + x[1] * x[0];
} We also support functions that return a float value: fn g(x: &[f32]) -> f32 { x[0] * x[0] + x[1] * x[0]
}

